message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
title: "VoxVerity: Measuring, Explaining, and Attempting to Close the Audio Deepfake Generalization Gap"
authors:
  - family-names: Vaidya
    given-names: Tejas
date-released: 2026-07-20
url: "https://github.com/Tejasvaidya10/VoxVerity"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Tejasvaidya10/VoxVerity"
license: MIT
type: software
keywords:
  - audio deepfake detection
  - anti-spoofing
  - generalization
  - explainable AI
  - self-supervised learning
  - ASVspoof
abstract: >
  A research study measuring the benchmark-to-real-world generalization gap
  in audio deepfake detection, diagnosing its mechanism via per-speaker
  failure analysis and an LLM explainability layer, testing a
  pre-registered hypothesis about the mechanism via training-time channel
  augmentation, and reporting a decisive negative result from an SSL
  front-end fine-tuning attempt. Full report in REPORT.md.
